      "id": "5a93c517_25c83254",
      "file_path": "policy-endpoints/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/drools/event/comm/bus/internal/SingleThreadedBusTopicSource.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 129,
      "message": "For topics used by pooled controllers, we need the consumerGroup to be the same across all JVM instances, while the consumerInstance must be different across all instances.  With this strategy, only the consumerGroup need be specified in the property file.  Where this behavior is NOT needed, the property file can specify a consumerInstance of \"0\" (or just let it default to a UUID).",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 811,
        "name": "Jim Hahn",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jrh3@att.com",
        "username": "jrh3"
