      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 129,
      "message": "If you don't mind, let's change the \n\nthis.consumerInstance = uuid \n\nto \n\nthis.consumerInstance = NetworkUtil.getHostname() or something like that, I don't recall the exact name, it is in policy-util package (provided it does not carry relevance in the pooling work) \n\nIt is good to have something descriptive, and that's the point of the consumerId.   When working with DMaaP folks, it would be very useful I think, when doing debugging on the DMaaP side to know exactly the identity of the pdp-d making the query.",
